<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0300 </DOCNO><TEXT>Diagnostic in vivo radioisotope thyroid investigations after the administrationof /sup 132/I - sodium iodide are carried out in Poland very rarely.In this paper two calculation methods of absorbed organ dose as dependenton age are presented. The effective dose equivalents and collective doseequivalents are calculated. The results indicate that these investigationscarry a relatively high ionizing radiation hazard. The values obtainedare compared with those for NaI(/sup 132/I). 7 refs., 3 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>